body:
I implemented your proposals @uschindler. I kept the definition of default and solrj java versions in main `build.gradle` for better visibility (needed to move it above the sourcing of `globals.gradle`) instead of burying it in other code. 

@HoustonPutman Which other modules are you thinking about, except the `solrj-*` ones?

IntelliJ is not good at sef-configuring language level, deleting `.idea`, it does not pick up the level to use for each module, any idea how to fix?

@cpoerschke is absolutely right, I added it "the hacky way". I'll extract the config setting the proper way 👍

With that, a unit test is easy to add @epugh 👍

I'll update the docs also as soon as I'm back at my desk (after Easter)

> @HoustonPutman Which other modules are you thinking about, except the `solrj-*` ones?

@janhoy Sorry I missed this, I'm thinking about the ones that would be used by SolrJ, like `hadoop-auth`, or `jwt-auth`. Or more security ones coming in the future.

Definitely not a blocker for this, but something to think about in the future, when we get these auth schemes working better with things like the CLI and SolrJ
